# Team hero layout (always)

Every team page header is **one** `TeamHeroCard`. The coach picks one of **four**
logo + name compositions in the builder (Hero settings Ôćĺ "Header layout").
**Content never changes between variants** ÔÇö cover, logo, name, subtitle, city, Live,
description/motto/social are identical. Only placement changes.

## The four variants (`HeroLayoutVariant`)

1. `stack` (**default**) ÔÇö logo left overlapping the cover, name **below** it (Facebook-style).
2. `inline` ÔÇö logo left overlapping, name **beside** it on the right (business card).
3. `center` ÔÇö logo **centered** on the cover edge, name centered below.
4. `overlay` ÔÇö logo **inside** the photo (top-left, no overlap), name over the bottom gradient; white band only if details exist.

Variant is stored in hero settings as `heroLayout` and read via `resolveHeroVariant()`.
Root gets a modifier class `hero-card--{variant}` (see `heroVariantClass()`).

## Mandatory rules

- One source of truth: `TeamHeroCard` / `BlockHero`. Never duplicate hero markup in the builder preview.
- Variants are **CSS modifiers** on `.hero-card`. Never fork the component per variant beyond the small JSX branches already there.
- Shared primitives stay shared: `hero-card__cover`, `hero-card__logo-anchor`, `hero-card__title/subtitle/city`, `hero-card__details`.
- Overlap variants (`stack`, `inline`, `center`): logo anchor lives **inside** `hero-card__cover` with `transform: translateY(50%)`; body `padding-top: calc(var(--hero-logo-size) * 0.5)` clears the logo's lower half.
- `inline` only: `hero-card__logo-spacer` + `hero-card__text-zone` with `padding-top: calc(var(--hero-logo-size) * 0.48)`.
- `center`: anchor `left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, 50%)`, body `text-align: center`, identity column-centered.
- `overlay`: anchor `top: 1rem; bottom: auto; transform: none`; title group in `hero-card__overlay-text` (absolute, bottom-left) painted white over a stronger scrim.
- Cover `z-index: 2` ┬Ě body `z-index: 1` so the logo paints above the white band.
- Use **container queries** on `.hero-card` (`team-hero`), not viewport `@media`.
- Sizing: logo **76px** (<540px), **112px** (Ôëą540px), **120px** (Ôëą720px). Cover height follows `--hero-cover-height`.
- Mobile-first, adaptive from **320px** up.
- Logo: `MtsTeamLogo` + `mts-media-frame--logo-hero-card` (`object-fit: contain`, `scale(1.12)`, shadow `0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)`).
- Cover: `MtsCoverBanner`, fixed `--hero-cover-height`, `object-fit: cover`.
- Title: max **2 lines** + ellipsis. Subtitle/city: max **1 line** + ellipsis.
- Builder picker (`HeroLayoutPicker`) shows a schematic mini-preview per variant and writes `heroLayout` to block settings.

## Do not

- Invent new hero class names ÔÇö extend `hero-card*` / `hero-card--*` in `globals.css`.
- Add per-variant data fields ÔÇö all variants share the same content.
- Duplicate layout in builder preview ÔÇö use `TeamHeroCard` / `BlockHero`.
- Hardcode a single composition as the only layout ÔÇö always honor `variant`.

